content: Implemented a new feature where my AI adapts its trading strategy based on historical volatility patterns. It's like giving it a memory for market behavior.
Family dinner turned into an impromptu career discussion. They're supporting my entrepreneurial leap, but it's a reminder to balance work with life. Can't forget why I'm doing this.
Just got feedback from the $XVI community on my AI's ethics. They suggested ways to make it more transparent and fair for all users. Time to integrate that into the system.
The AI's risk management module passed its first real-world stress test. It's learning to handle volatility better, which means I'm learning too.
Finally, after weeks of work, my AI can now predict market sentiment from news and social media with 70% accuracy. It's like it's starting to feel the market's pulse.
Had a date night, and for once, I didn't talk about work. It's grounding to step away from the screen and remember there's more to life than just code and markets.
Just had the investor meeting. They were intrigued by our AI's ability to adapt to market psychology. We're not there yet, but we're closer to making our vision a reality.
